dismissalText.commentary: Misbah-ul-Haq c †Ronchi b Henry 47 (65b 2x4 2x6 72m) SR: 72.3

dismissalComment.html: they appeal for a caught behind and Illingworth immediately lifts the finger.. the bowler had actually given up on the appeal -- he had his hands on his head. It was only Ronchi appealing. But the bowler is pleasantly surprised. It was a bouncer again and Misbah went for a hook, but missed. This one goes over his left shoulder and looked good in the real time. Misbah reviews it immediately. The replays look like they would support Illingworth and that is what the decision is. Misbah has to go, despite him gesturing that it was off his fore-arm. He is not happy. But Henry has four now

dismissalText.commentary: Kane Williamson not out 70 (91b 7x4 0x6 127m) SR: 76.92
Anton Devcich run out (Mohammad Hafeez/Haris Sohail) 58 (66b 8x4 0x6 102m) SR: 87.87

dismissalComment.html: what a waste! Dev is hugely disappointed... He played a nice reverse paddle straight to short third man.. Williamson wanted the run and he was charging down the pitch. Anton Dev started late and his only hope was the fielder going for the wrong end. It didn't happen and Sohail whips off the bails

Sohail strikes, his maiden wicket in ODIs! What a big one this is! It was not short enough but Taylor went for the cut nonetheless, he underedges it to the keeper. Taylor was looking like he was about to walk, but he waited an extra second.. the umpire took his time and finally sent him on his way

another one for Sohail! This is the mirror image of what Williamson did two balls ago - steps out of the crease and looks to chip through wide long-on, but unfortunately for Latham, the fielder - Tanvir - was in the right place.
this has to be a bonus wicket! Tossed up delivery outside off, Anderson goes for the big sweep, but this is too full for it and he drags it from outside off to his stumps. Number three for Sohail

headshotImage.caption: Dean Brownlie player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Dean Brownlie player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalComment.html: and double B does the double S! Boom Boom's special delivery, which doesn't do anything.. just keeps coming in and Backfoot Brownlie just got cramped for room. It hits the top of middle. The Shahid Slider did the job there

oh what a stunner! Sohail Tanvir takes a blinder at long off to buoy Pakistan. Ronchi went for a big hit on this flighted delivery, but this one turned and messed up with the batsman's timing.. he ended up chipping it towards long-off. Tanvir had to run forward and dive full length - always difficult - to grab this smartly. What a strike this is!

headshotImage.longCaption: Matt Henry player page headshot cutout, 2021

commentTextItems.html: goes for the reverse-sweep but this one slides off the glove/pad down to the boundary.. Over? No. Afridi wants a review. Was he hit in front of the off there? Can't say really. If he has missed, and it's out, it's another wicket for Haris Sohail, so important for him. What fun right at the end! It's missing off... so it's Game Over officially. Signalled four leg byes

commentPostTextItems.html: Another close contest between the team and it's a fair result that the series is level. Thanks for yours comments and feedback. We will be back for more in a couple of days. Ciao ciao.

"We missed our chance in our batting," says Afridi. "We lost three wickets early, we should have crossed 280. We didn't bowl consistently either when we needed wickets. We can't think of the ones who are injured, we have to manage with what we have and produce results with them."

Mohammad Hafeez gets an award for hitting sixes, Kane Williamson gets a cheque for being the best batsman, Anton Devcich gets an award for the most colourful innings, Adam Milne keeps taking those awards for being the fastest bowler (he should really get that money .. all of it in one go), Luke Ronchi gets an award for the Bonus Shot (whatever that means), Matt Henry gets one for outstanding award. Finally, Kane Williamson is the Man of the Match.

"Credit goes to our bowlers on a fast outfield and slow pitch," says Williamson. "I ran my mate out, so actually should give the award to them. We are not entirely happy to chop and change. Sometimes we have to take measures. I didn't think my bowling today was appropriate, the seamers were doing well. The first game, we played quite well, missed it by small margins. So it was pleasing to win this by winning those small margins.

A comfortable win for New Zealand in the end, their first-ever in an ODI in Sharjah and second here within the last few days after that series-equalising win in the Tests. The chase was bookended by two partnerships: a 103-run one between Anton Devcich and Dean Brownlie and the 58-run one between Kane Williamson and Luke Ronchi. Williamson stayed solid through a mid-innings wobble and stayed unbeaten till the end. Pakistan would probably look back to the start of their innings in the afternoon. They won the toss, but lost their first three wickets cheaply. It was a catch-up game from there on. New Zealand's seamers were terrific today. They bowled to a plan, bowled with pace, and bowled short to share the ten wickets between them, quite an achievement given the placid nature of the pitch. New Zealand have now levelled the series with three more to play.

commentTextItems.html: dropped! By the keeper. The batsman came down the pitch, but gets a thick outside edge. Tough one for the keeper there. They also take a run off the deflection
flatter, shorter, wider, Williamson gets a toe end to it as he looks to punch it through cover
he takes off for a single to mid-off with a quick push
tossed up outside off, the batsman comes down the pitch and squeezes it to deep cover
he comes down the pitch and chips the length delivery towards deep midwicket
he stays back and clips it off his hips to fine leg
he comes forward and pushes the length delivery calmly to deep point

commentPostTextItems.html: DanielAlexander: "Kane Williamson is the next Mahela Jayawardene #AllClass "

commentPreTextItems.html: Martin S: "Sounds like Irfan has been incredibly unlucky not to take a wicket. If Pakistan can have both him and Junaid fit for the World Cup their chances will be greatly improved."

commentTextItems.html: slower delivery on off, the batsman chops it to the wicketkeeper

commentPreTextItems.html: Pakistan news: Umar Gul has a bruised tendon in his left ankle, seems to have aggravated his old injury. Misbah-ul-Haq will be assessed tomorrow

commentTextItems.html: shortish delivery, the batsman looks to play it towards point but gets a thick outside edge towards third man
goes to the off side and this time he flicks it over the infield, behind square now. Shafiq slides and tries to keep it in, but his foot is touching the rope. So four more
fuller delivery on off, Vettori walks across to the off side and flicks it through square leg with a lot of timing.. Superb shot
short and wide, Williamson gets up on his toes and crashes it behind point for four more

commentPostTextItems.html: Umair: "Is that a miscalculation? Shouldn't Tanveer be bowling the 44th for them to not need an over from Haris Sohail? Or do they hope to finish it in 49?" ---- Or use Haris Sohail

commentTextItems.html: quicker delivery outside off, the batsman looks for a cut but misses
short delivery, Williamson gets inside the line and pulls it down to fine leg. The fielder - Tanvir - makes a valiant effort but can't keep it in this time
superb delivery! It cuts in away from the batsman, beating the outside edge as Williamson pushes forward

commentPreTextItems.html: A slip and a short cover point in place

commentTextItems.html: back of length on off, the batsman pushes it through cover for his first runs
length delivery outside off, Williamson calmly dabs it to third man and jogs to the other end
tossed up on the stumps, Williamson eases it to long on for a single
he is solidly behind this flatter delivery, defends it to midwicket

dismissalText.commentary: Ahmed Shehzad c †Ronchi b Henry 0 (5b 0x4 0x6 3m) SR: 0

dismissalComment.html: first full delivery fetches the wicket! What a blow. He was keeping the batsmen back  and slips in the fuller one to surprise Shehzad. The batsman was a touch slow to come forward and gives a simple chance to the keeper

dismissalText.commentary: Younis Khan c Taylor b McClenaghan 6 (6b 1x4 0x6 9m) SR: 100

dismissalComment.html: that no-ball hasn't hurt much! There is no celebration from Mitch this time.. They are checking for a no-ball. Younis was stuck in the crease and pokes at an angled delivery, only manages to edge it to Taylor at first slip. This one's fine. Absolutely fine.

headshotImage.longCaption: Asad Shafiq player page headshot cutout, 2021

headshotImage.caption: Asad Shafiq player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Asad Shafiq player page headshot cutout, 2021

headshotImage.caption: Matt Henry player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Matt Henry player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Asad Shafiq b Henry 1 (5b 0x4 0x6 11m) SR: 20

dismissalComment.html: full, fast and furious! The stumps have been splayed. This is exhilarating stuff from New Zealand. Henry pushes this further up and keeps it on the middle stump line.. Shafiq wanted to flick it but that was a bit too quick, flies through the gate and whacks the stumps

dismissalText.commentary: Haris Sohail c Taylor b Anderson 33 (45b 2x4 1x6 67m) SR: 73.33

dismissalComment.html: what a waste that is! Sohail has pulled this short delivery straight into the hands of short midwicket! Taylor was looking into the sun but reacted quickly enough to hold on to that. A little better connection and it would have been safe. Anderson is all smiles.. he knows it's a wicket for him that's come from nowhere

headshotImage.caption: Matt Henry player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Matt Henry player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Mohammad Hafeez c Latham b Henry 76 (92b 9x4 1x6 149m) SR: 82.6

dismissalComment.html: Whoa! Big hit but he is gone. A zero sum game. He swivels and plays a fine pull.. but plays it straight to the man at deep midwicket. The fielder doesn't have to move an inch.

headshotImage.caption: Matt Henry player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Matt Henry player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Misbah-ul-Haq c †Ronchi b Henry 47 (65b 2x4 2x6 72m) SR: 72.3

dismissalComment.html: they appeal for a caught behind and Illingworth immediately lifts the finger.. the bowler had actually given up on the appeal -- he had his hands on his head. It was only Ronchi appealing. But the bowler is pleasantly surprised. It was a bouncer again and Misbah went for a hook, but missed. This one goes over his left shoulder and looked good in the real time. Misbah reviews it immediately. The replays look like they would support Illingworth and that is what the decision is. Misbah has to go, despite him gesturing that it was off his fore-arm. He is not happy. But Henry has four now

dismissalText.commentary: Shahid Afridi c Vettori b Milne 27 (14b 1x4 3x6 20m) SR: 192.85

dismissalComment.html: ooh Lala.. Afridi doesn't know when to apply brakes! Keeps going for the big swing but there is no room on this one and all he can do is top-edge the pull. Vettori at mid-off gobbles up the skier

dismissalText.commentary: Wahab Riaz c Taylor b Milne 14 (19b 1x4 0x6 18m) SR: 73.68

dismissalComment.html: Milne takes his second with a quick short of length delivery.. Riaz rose up with it but could only manage and edge straight to first slip. Fourth career wicket for Milne

dismissalText.commentary: Sarfaraz Ahmed c Latham b McClenaghan 23 (31b 0x4 0x6 65m) SR: 74.19

dismissalComment.html: he is gone! Sarfraz has had to wait throughout this innings to open his arms. Last two overs, he thought this was the time. He looks to swing the length delivery down the ground but gets a big top edge that swirls in the air and settles down at cover. No boundaries today for him

dismissalText.commentary: Sohail Tanvir lbw b McClenaghan 14 (10b 2x4 0x6 16m) SR: 140

dismissalComment.html: he misses the full toss and he has to go. Illingworth raises his finger. It hit him on the thigh pad but that was a good call from the umpire. It was hitting the middle. Tanvir wants to review it, but there are none left

headshotImage.caption: Dean Brownlie player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Dean Brownlie player page headshot cutout, 2021

headshotImage.caption: Dean Brownlie player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Dean Brownlie player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Dean Brownlie b Shahid Afridi 47 (61b 8x4 0x6 77m) SR: 77.04

dismissalComment.html: and double B does the double S! Boom Boom's special delivery, which doesn't do anything.. just keeps coming in and Backfoot Brownlie just got cramped for room. It hits the top of middle. The Shahid Slider did the job there

dismissalText.commentary: Anton Devcich run out (Mohammad Hafeez/Haris Sohail) 58 (66b 8x4 0x6 102m) SR: 87.87

dismissalComment.html: what a waste! Dev is hugely disappointed... He played a nice reverse paddle straight to short third man.. Williamson wanted the run and he was charging down the pitch. Anton Dev started late and his only hope was the fielder going for the wrong end. It didn't happen and Sohail whips off the bails

dismissalText.commentary: Kane Williamson not out 70 (91b 7x4 0x6 127m) SR: 76.92
Ross Taylor c †Sarfaraz Ahmed b Haris Sohail 2 (3b 0x4 0x6 9m) SR: 66.66

dismissalComment.html: Sohail strikes, his maiden wicket in ODIs! What a big one this is! It was not short enough but Taylor went for the cut nonetheless, he underedges it to the keeper. Taylor was looking like he was about to walk, but he waited an extra second.. the umpire took his time and finally sent him on his way

headshotImage.caption: Sohail Tanvir player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Sohail Tanvir player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.long: c Sohail Tanvir b Haris Sohail
dismissalText.commentary: Tom Latham c Sohail Tanvir b Haris Sohail 3 (7b 0x4 0x6 11m) SR: 42.85

dismissalComment.html: another one for Sohail! This is the mirror image of what Williamson did two balls ago - steps out of the crease and looks to chip through wide long-on, but unfortunately for Latham, the fielder - Tanvir - was in the right place.

dismissalText.commentary: Corey Anderson b Haris Sohail 10 (10b 0x4 1x6 17m) SR: 100

dismissalComment.html: this has to be a bonus wicket! Tossed up delivery outside off, Anderson goes for the big sweep, but this is too full for it and he drags it from outside off to his stumps. Number three for Sohail

headshotImage.caption: Sohail Tanvir player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Sohail Tanvir player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.long: c Sohail Tanvir b Shahid Afridi
dismissalText.commentary: Luke Ronchi c Sohail Tanvir b Shahid Afridi 36 (32b 6x4 0x6 46m) SR: 112.5

dismissalComment.html: oh what a stunner! Sohail Tanvir takes a blinder at long off to buoy Pakistan. Ronchi went for a big hit on this flighted delivery, but this one turned and messed up with the batsman's timing.. he ended up chipping it towards long-off. Tanvir had to run forward and dive full length - always difficult - to grab this smartly. What a strike this is!

dismissalText.commentary: Daniel Vettori not out 13 (8b 2x4 0x6 19m) SR: 162.5
